                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102 Tientsin/634: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-18T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 18, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 18—3:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. My 56, April 18, 10 a.m.<note n="17" xml:id="d923fn17">Not printed.</note> In
                    a conversation with Vice Consul Yuni yesterday concerning the numerous present
                    barrier difficulties of Americans, the Japanese Consular official who usually
                    handles such matters asserted that attitude of American Government as evidenced
                    by abrogation of the treaty and in other ways which he declined to specify has
                    been designed to prevent a settlement of the Tientsin questions under discussion
                    between the British and the Japanese authorities (see paragraphs, my telegram
                    No. 277, November 22, 6 p.m., 1939<note n="18" xml:id="d923fn18">
                        <ref target="frus1939v04#pg_252">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1939, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p. 252</ref>.</note>).</p>
                <p>Repeated to Chungking, Peiping, air mail to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
